post: {'type': 'con', 'text': 'One can imagine that an inebriated cannabis user may leave the house less often and therefore spend less money. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Currently, in the USA, there is a [pharmaceutical opioid crisis](https://www.cfr.org/backgrounder/us-opioid-epidemic). Drug companies and legal policies cannot be trusted to protect citizens. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs being legalized would allow the injured victims \\(or their heirs\\) of fraudulently/irresponsibly cut/marketed drugs to legally and publicly sue the manufacturer/distributor for damages, thereby using market pressures to better assure product/service quality/safety. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition has lead to [high incarceration rates](https://www.politifact.com/truth-o-meter/statements/2016/jul/10/cory-booker/how-war-drugs-affected-incarceration-rates/) of otherwise inoffensive citizens. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Some adults may sell drugs to underaged people to make profit. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Incarceration does not treat addiction; the money spent on incarcerated non-violent drug offenders could be instead used to fund addiction treatment.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '"Giving up" is preferable to endlessly pursuing an unobtainable goal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs would significantly decrease social stigma and discrimination against users who have been incarcerated for employment and education opportunities.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Further studies on the "Rat Park" experiment discussed in the video [have found](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rat_Park#Reaction_to_the_experiment) social isolation is not necessary for addiction.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Drug legalization will stimulate local and national economies. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Criminals will face competition from legal growers with lower shipping costs, which will drive prices down.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Something being illegal makes the entire area "tainted." Talking about how to do something illegal is seen as encouraging said activity, and "sending the wrong signals."'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is undeniable; however, the same is true whether drugs are legal or not. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Nixon's war on drugs [was started](https://www.cnn.com/2016/03/23/politics/john-ehrlichman-richard-nixon-drug-war-blacks-hippie/index.html) to target blacks and hippies."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many constitutions and legal frameworks promote personal autonomy. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug prohibition might be inspired by some kind of racism but abandoning it would not necessarily mean an improvement of the situation for those incarcerated or addicted to drugs. There are still many other systematic racial issues unrelated to drug prohibition.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Governments manipulate citizens by spreading biased information about drugs and thereby interfering with their choices. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Smoking](https://www.cancer.org/cancer/cancer-causes/tobacco-and-cancer/secondhand-smoke.html) puts the drugs into the air, meaning non-consenting people take the drug as well.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'One solution for recreational availability of such drugs could be to require that they emit an unmistakable coloring or odour/taste when dissolved in a drink.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "The long-term effects of many drugs are not yet fully understood. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'People in poor health or overdosing on drugs are often not taken to receive medical attention for fear of criminal prosecution.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'It will destroy jobs for drug enforcement agencies, lawyers, judges, police, prison wardens. There is a whole industry depending on it.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'When obtaining drugs legally people can be sure that the drugs are pure and accurately measured. With the illegal drug market drugs are often mis-sold, inaccurately measured or cut with other substances.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization does not treat addicts, treatment and prevention of the addiction do. Both of which can be done with drugs remaining illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'It is likely that a small group who are motivated not to take hard drugs solely because they are illegal would then try drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "This is perhaps a fantastic way to prevent drug abuse in children and, hopefully therefore, adults too. However, it doesn't contribute to bringing down cartels or allow healthy adults to use recreational drugs in the safest possible way."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The law regulation of the drug's market will standardize the quality of the products, and their safety, creating incentives for the consumers to prefer to deal in the legal market. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This limits what we know about these compounds as well as to what length we are able to develop treatments for those struggling with addiction \\(physical and mental\\) as well as treatment for acute toxicity.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization runs the danger of increased drug use that could impair people from doing jobs safely, making work places more dangerous.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Research chemicals, which are used as [date rape drugs](https://drugabuse.com/date-rape-drugs/), are constantly evolving and changing formulations to escape existing regulation. It is unlikely that the law would be able to control all of them. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs should not be a prerequisite for better education. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs may also alter the strength of which learning \\(permanent changes of neural activity\\) reacts to such rewards.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Drug users will encourage other people, who do not know how to handle drugs and/or aren't smart and/or mature enough to try it. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalization of recreational drug use is not necessary for legalization of expanded drug research. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Organized crime would find themselves without a cash-flow and resort to much more violent kidnapping and extortion. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Suicide rates may increase as overdose will be an easily accessible option.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Governments would be able to check what cutting agents are used within the drugs, meaning they will be safer as potentially harmful cutting agents would be banned. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The responsible use of drugs for recreational purposes does not harm others and therefore can not be considered immoral. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '"Profit for companies" is better than "profit for criminal cartels", if those are the two choices.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will decrease the number of fatal overdoses by giving each user a safe dose of the drugs by regulating the drugs. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Individuals who do not seek out dangerous activities shouldn't be punished for those who do. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs has criminalized a large number of otherwise innocent individuals.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'It would be unethical to bring in revenue from taxing drugs as it exploits those who suffer from addiction.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Former inmates are significantly more at risk of drug-related mortality than the general population.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs will create jobs \\(i.e. people selling in certified shops, people in labs etc.\\).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The government would be giving up authority to empower the individual. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Cocaine is [highly addictive](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cocaine_dependence) and easy to become dependent on. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing something means including it the current system of business oversight and regulation as other legal activities. This means documenting purchases and monetary transactions, as well as filing and paying taxes. This means more control over where drugs come from and money goes, rather than would be the case under prohibition or decriminalization.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Producers and distributors are not able to control how consumers use their products. Therefore, legalising the sale and possession of drugs necessarily would allow for this kind of abuse to increase easily despite the illegality of forcing another person to ingest them.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the long run, the standing of the U.S. government did not suffer from ending the Alcohol Prohibition in the 1930s. Any potential reputational damage from ending marijuana or other prohibitions would be fleeting.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Dangerous substitute drugs will be contained. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help reduce social rifts.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[In 2017](https://www.kialo.com/all-drugs-should-be-legalized-7100/7100.0=7100.1+7100.297), there were more direct deaths from alcohol consumption than from drug consumption.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalization will not drastically affect drug use. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "A lack of visible violence doesn't mean that companies are not behaving in a manner which is damaging to society. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Hallucinogens such as LSD and magic mushrooms have been used to create many great artworks. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs being legalized would allow the injured victims \\(or their heirs\\) of fraudulently/irresponsibly cut/marketed drugs to legally and publicly sue the manufacturer/distributor for damages, thereby using market pressures to better assure product/service quality/safety. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs being legal shifts the focus of the police from investigating crimes where individuals damaged others instead of themselves. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "It is hard to determine whether the drugs actually allowed these artists to make these pieces of art or whether they just happened also to be using drugs because they had troubled minds. Sober people can be great artists. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs can be used to abuse others or commit crimes.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalizing drugs will not automatically remove the prejudice. If people see those on drugs being violent or a nuisance to society, the prejudice will likely remain. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the Andes, [coca](https://nacla.org/article/beat-goes-us-war-coca), a sacred plant harmful when mass produced as a cash crop, has replaced the production of fruits and vegetables.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs will improve overall safety by containing criminal opportunities.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Medical professionals have expressed [negative attitudes](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23490450) in treating illegal substance abusers, which subsequently negatively impacts their treatment. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Benzodiazepines are [readily available](http://w-bad.org/statistics/) in most countries for common complaints like insomnia, jet lag and performance anxiety, and are actually more effective at increasing the effects of alcohol than barbiturates.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Incarceration of drug users impacts their families.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'One can imagine that an inebriated cannabis user may leave the house less often and therefore spend less money. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Addictions can lead to improper care of children, relatives, or any person \\(even animals\\) who depends on the user.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While some might overestimate the revenue, there still will be revenue. If it is 1/2 or 1/3 of those naive estimates, it is still revenue, and it still increases the government coffers.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Making things safer will benefit all users, while a false sense of safety only applies to a minority. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Under prohibition, anything related to drugs use \\(like paraphernalia\\) would both be evidence of a crime and likely to be confiscated if found by police — this disincentive carrying anything other than the bare necessities to drug use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalization will not drastically affect drug use. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Professional addiction treatment is usually [expensive](https://www.addictioncenter.com/rehab-questions/cost-of-drug-and-alcohol-treatment/). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Just because there are other systematic racial issues does not mean we cannot challenge this particular racist law.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legal drugs make it easier for criminals to coerce prostitutes through drug addiction with the state being able to do less to rehabilitate them forcefully. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "In countries where using marijuana is legal or allowed, [smoking games](https://honestmarijuana.com/weed-games/) have arisen to get more stoned/high more quickly. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Selling harmful products is a poor long-term business strategy, as can be seen with tobacco companies. It only works as long as there is uncertainty in their harms. When the harms become apparent, people will take measures to stop using it as well as take measures to stop others from using it.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "As long as the taxes don't surpass the higher costs of the black market businesses, there is no reason to believe that legal drugs would be more expensive. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Allowing people to become addicted merely so we can understand addiction is socially and medically irresponsible. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The effects of smoking are slow and not always visible; this means people are not as aware of them.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This could lead individuals into a false sense of safety when it comes to drug use.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The anxiety induced by the threat of arrest can be a cause for the violent paranoia episodes some users experience while under the influence emotion enhancing substances.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of all drugs gives the possibility to control the age group of people participating in the drugs. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs are highly addictive; [addiction is defined as a disease](https://www.centeronaddiction.org/what-addiction/addiction-disease) by most medical associations.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many poets have made works under the influence of drugs. For example, [the romantic poets used opium and the Beat poets used hallucinogens](https://www.huffingtonpost.com/john-lundberg/drugs-literature-poetry_b_1011124.html).'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The [majority](http://www.independent.co.uk/news/habits-most-drug-users-are-happy-successful-people-with-a-taste-for-the-good-life-1292155.html) of young individuals consuming illegal substances lead fulfilling and successful lives.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Making things safer is always preferable.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is no guarantee that a similar legal compound will act the same way as the original one.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is better to educate people on how to use valuable-yet-dangerous things safely than to ban their use entirely.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The responsible use of drugs for recreational purposes does not harm others and therefore can not be considered immoral. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "When drugs are legalised, people who are addicted may feel more comfortable seeking help and support as they won't be viewed as criminals in the way they currently are. I believe all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The law regulation of the drug's market will standardize the quality of the products, and their safety, creating incentives for the consumers to prefer to deal in the legal market. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The fact that legalising drugs would not "end all crime" does not means that it would not damage criminal organizations. It\'s a step in the right direction to reduce their power.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The criminalization of drug use is the major agitator of the economic rifts caused by drug use: illegal drug use leads to arrests which lead to arrest records and the socially imposed inability to self-produce wealth.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Education and information might not be enough to ensure thoughtful drug use.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is because the US prison system is [privately owned.](https://smartasset.com/mortgage/the-economics-of-the-american-prison-system) Incentive structures mean that running prisons can only be profitable with high rates of incarceration.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Governments invested a lot of money trying to cease drug use by everyone. It failed miserably. Not only it is not the most efficient way, but it is not even achievable.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow for effective tools and strategies to fight criminal organizations.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Governments would be able to check what cutting agents are used within the drugs, meaning they will be safer as potentially harmful cutting agents would be banned. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Addictive drugs increasingly reduce one's ability to do without them, and therefore they can inhibit freedom. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
